Ingredients of Cold Coffee

2 cup milk
2 1/2 teaspoon coffee
2 tablespoon fresh cream

1 teaspoon Honey
2 tablespoon vanilla ice cream
1/2 cup Ice cubes

Step 1

Put ice cubes in the jar of the blender, and add coffee, milk, honey, cream and about two table spoon ice cream. If you donâ€™t have a blender just take a shaker put some milk, add honey, coffee, cream and give it a nice stir and then shake it! You like it creamy add some fresh cream and shake it well.

Step 2

Blend it in the mixer, take some ice cubes and then pour it in glasses. Put a scoop of vanilla ice cream and top it with some chocolate syrup, nuts and raisins. Relish this recipe with some savoury delight!